FT  09 FEB 94 / Chancellor outlines reasons for cut
Mr Kenneth Clarke, the chancellor, issued the following statement on
yesterday's cut in interest rates.
'After discussion with the governor of the Bank of England on the prospects
for inflation, I have decided that it would be appropriate to reduce
interest rates by a further 0.25 per cent. Inflation has been lower than
expected. Looking ahead inflationary pressures appear subdued.
'With interest rates and inflation at historically low levels, the time is
right to reduce the magnitude of interest rate changes. The reduction of
0.25 per cent continues the government's prudent approach to monetary policy
and its commitment to low inflation.'
